- even if an existing directory is owned by the executing user, it may be globally writable before keystoneclient chmods it</p>
<p>The attached patch fixes these issues (including ttx&#x27;s suggestion) but fails unit testing because they use a signing_dir w/ 0755. Feedback/review on the fix itself appreciated in the mean time.</p>
<p>I also think this should move to oslo.fileutils eventually.</p></div>
    
    
    
